gov.nih.nlm.nls.skr
Class GenericObject

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.nls.skr.GenericObject

public class GenericObject
extends java.lang.Object

Generic job specific fields and handling routines.

NOTES:
1. Generic jobs can only be Batch jobs, we don't support Interactive Generic jobs.

2. Generic jobs must have commands that reside in /nfsvol/nls/bin
Specified via the Batch_Command field. For example, 'setField("Batch_Command", "MTI -opt1_DCMS -E")'.

3. Commands for the Generic jobs must not have ".." embedded in their path

4. Generic jobs can be normal (without validation), or with validation where the Scheduler expects an "<< EOT >>" end of result marker so it can verify it received a complete result.

5. Generic jobs also allow you to specify any special environment
variables you might need inorder to run your command. Specified via the Batch_Env field. For example, 'setField("Batch_Env", "NLS=/nfsvol/nls#CC=gcc")'. Where each environment variable is separated by a "#". Note that these are not needed to run the MTI command in the above example, but are here for illustrative purposes only.

Version:
1.0, September 18, 2006
Author:
Jim Mork

validBatchCommand

private boolean validBatchCommand()
Validating the Generic Batch command. This routine ensures that the command specified actually resides in the /nfsvol/nls/bin directory and doesn't contain any ".." path redirections. If both of these conditions are met, validBatchCommand returns true.

Returns:
boolean determination of whether command is valid or not
